<subSubSection id="E497654DFFA3523BFF3EFB06FECDCC4A" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="AC3236C6FFA3523BFF3EFB06FC28CE8E" blockId="28.[151,1437,153,1583]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FFA3523BFF3EFB06FEDCCEC6" bold="true" box="[199,335,1160,1187]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="6B8D4D45FFA3523BFEAFFB07FD8CCEC6" authority="Villamizar &amp; Fernández &amp; Vivallo, 2020" authorityName="Villamizar &amp; Fernández &amp; Vivallo" authorityYear="2020" box="[342,543,1161,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romeroi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FFA3523BFEAFFB07FD8CCEC6" box="[342,543,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">Xylocopa romeroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FFA3523BFDDEFB07FDF5CEC6" bold="true" box="[551,614,1161,1187]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="85CA57AFFFA3523BFDDEFB07FDF5CEC6" box="[551,614,1161,1187]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is one of the largest species of the subgenus that have the base of labrum with three tubercles of similar length and not a single, large, capitate tuberculum as can be found in other large species as 
<taxonomicName id="6B8D4D45FFA3523BFF11FB5CFE11CE8E" authority="Villamizar &amp; Fernández &amp; Vivallo, 2020" authorityName="Villamizar &amp; Fernández &amp; Vivallo" authorityYear="2020" box="[232,386,1234,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auriventris" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FFA3523BFF11FB5CFE11CE8E" box="[232,386,1234,1259]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">X. auriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FFA3523BFE70FB5FFE5BCE8E" bold="true" box="[393,456,1233,1259]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="85CA57AFFFA3523BFE70FB5FFE5BCE8E" box="[393,456,1233,1259]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6B8D4D45FFA3523BFE2FFB5CFDF3CE8E" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[470,608,1233,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiata">
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FFA3523BFE2FFB5CFDF3CE8E" box="[470,608,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">X. dimidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6B8D4D45FFA3523BFD96FB5CFD65CE8E" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1874" box="[623,758,1233,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FFA3523BFD96FB5CFD65CE8E" box="[623,758,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">X. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6B8D4D45FFA3523BFCD5FB5CFC20CE8E" authorityName=": Smith" authorityYear="1854" box="[812,947,1233,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simillima">
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FFA3523BFCD5FB5CFC20CE8E" box="[812,947,1233,1259]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">X. simillima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AC3236C6FFA3523BFF3EFB7BFDC1CF82" blockId="28.[151,1437,153,1583]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">
This new species was collected approximately 100 years ago, remaining unstudied until now. A Colombian female from the department of 
<collectingRegion id="6E49F824FFA3523BFE0CFA97FDA8CF56" box="[501,571,1305,1331]" country="Colombia" name="Cauca" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">Cauca</collectingRegion>
contained in MNCN was identified by 
<bibRefCitation id="C81C4B37FFA3523BFC0EFA97FB69CF56" author="Dusmet-Alonso, J. M." box="[1015,1274,1305,1331]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" pagination="5 - 58" refId="ref30424" refString="Dusmet-Alonso, J. M. (1924) Las &quot; Xylocopa &quot; (Hymen. Apidae) en las colecciones de Madrid. Trabajos del Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales de Madrid, Serie Zoologica, 49, 5 - 58." type="journal article" year="1924">Dusmet-Alonso (1924)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName id="6B8D4D45FFA3523BFAD9FA94FA0FCF56" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1837" box="[1312,1436,1305,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateralis">
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FFA3523BFAD9FA94FA0FCF56" box="[1312,1436,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">X. lateralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the association by similarity with a Mexican male. We examined that specimen and it corresponds to a female of 
<taxonomicName id="6B8D4D45FFA3523BFF4FFAECFEBCCF1E" authority="Villamizar &amp; Fernández &amp; Vivallo, 2020" authorityName="Villamizar &amp; Fernández &amp; Vivallo" authorityYear="2020" box="[182,303,1378,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romeroi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FFA3523BFF4FFAECFEBCCF1E" box="[182,303,1378,1403]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">X. romeroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FFA3523BFECEFAEFFEE5CF1E" bold="true" box="[311,374,1377,1403]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="85CA57AFFFA3523BFECEFAEFFEE5CF1E" box="[311,374,1377,1403]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Curiously, Dusmet-Alonso (op. cit.) mentioned that the exemplar has strong violaceous highlights and only refers to the whitish hairs on lateral sides of last terga. The Mexican male was also examined and we think that it fits into the concept of 
<taxonomicName id="6B8D4D45FFA3523BFDD9FA24FD29CFA6" authorityName="Maidl" authorityYear="1912" box="[544,698,1450,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caviventris">
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FFA3523BFDD9FA24FD29CFA6" box="[544,698,1450,1475]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">X. caviventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than 
<taxonomicName id="6B8D4D45FFA3523BFD01FA24FCE0CFA6" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1837" box="[760,883,1449,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateralis">
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FFA3523BFD01FA24FCE0CFA6" box="[760,883,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">X. lateralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, its real identity can be solved with the study of more exemplars of that region.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AC3236C6FFA3523BFF3EFA7FFECDCC4A" blockId="28.[151,1437,153,1583]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">
The 
<typeStatus id="73368864FFA3523BFF03FA7FFECFCC6E" box="[250,348,1521,1547]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="73368864FFA3523BFE6DFA7FFE67CC6E" box="[404,500,1521,1547]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">paratype</typeStatus>
were collected in the Pacific region (Pacific domain 
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FFA3523BFBB2FA7CFB1ACC6E" box="[1099,1161,1522,1547]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="329">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="C81C4B37FFA3523BFB68FA7FFAA8CC6E" author="Morrone, J. J." box="[1169,1339,1521,1547]" pageId="28" pageNumber="329" pagination="1 - 110" refId="ref32894" refString="Morrone, J. J. (2014) Biogeographical regionalisation of the Neotropical region. Zootaxa, 3782, 1 - 110. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3782.1.1" type="journal article" year="2014">Morrone, 2014</bibRefCitation>
) and the male is unknown.
</paragraph>
